The behavior of $\Gamma(r)$ for a lGRB can be written \begin{equation}\label{eqn:gammar} \Gamma(r) = \begin{cases} \displaystyle \frac{r}{R_0} Acceleration Phase:  R_0 \leq r \leq R_s\end{equation}
\begin{equation}\displaystyle \eta Coasting Phase:  R_s \leq r \leq R_d\end{equation}
\begin{equation}\displaystyle \eta \left( \frac{r}{R_d} \right)^{-\frac{3}{2}} Deceleration Phase:  r \geq R_d \ , \end{cases}\end{equation} where $R_0$ is the starting radius of the jet, $R_s$ sets the coasting phase, $R_d$ sets the deceleration phase and $\eta$ represents the maximum of $\Gamma$ for a given burst.
